        <!-- Story / Logline -->
        <section id="story" class="content-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">STORY / LOGLINE</h2>
            <div class="container">
                <p class="logline-text">
                    Late 6th century South India. In the Cave of Destiny, two princes face a choice: the Magic Sword of
                    Pride or the Winged Armor of Awareness. Prince Raya seizes the Sword and becomes a tyrant emperor,
                    killing his brother Cheliya. Years later, Cheliya's son Ruthra—raised in secret as a masked
                    thief—discovers his father's relic and transforms into a gigantic Winged Yali. To end Raya's reign,
                    Ruthra must flood the Empire and face the Dark Sword in an epic battle where awareness conquers
                    aggression.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Mythology -->
        <section id="mythology" class="content-section alt-bg">
            <h2 class="section-title">MYTHOLOGY OF YAALI</h2>
            <div class="container grid-2">
                <div class="myth-panel">
                    <h3>The Cave of Destiny</h3>
                    <p>The sacred cave where two princes faced their choice: the Magic Sword (Pride/Aggression) or the
                        Winged Armor (Awareness). This moment shaped the fate of the Empire.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="myth-panel">
                    <h3>The Magic Sword</h3>
                    <p>A relic of Pride and Aggression. Chosen by Prince Raya, it grants immense power fueled by ego and
                        violence, transforming its wielder into a tyrant consumed by the Dark Sword's fire.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="myth-panel">
                    <h3>The Winged Armor</h3>
                    <p>A relic of Awareness and Peace. Chosen by Prince Cheliya, it grants the power to transform into a
                        gigantic Winged Yali—a divine warrior who observes before acting.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="myth-panel">
                    <h3>Yali Symbolism</h3>
                    <p>Ancient symbol from the Pazhi tribe, representing the bridge between mortal and divine. The Yali
                        embodies protection, power, and the wisdom to face fear with awareness.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Characters -->
        <section id="characters" class="content-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS</h2>
            <div class="container grid-4">
                <!-- Ruthra -->
                <div class="char-card">
                    <img src="images/Characters/Ruthra.png" alt="Ruthra" class="char-img">
                    <h3>Ruthra</h3>
                    <p class="role">Protagonist - The Winged Warrior</p>
                    <p class="bio">Son of Cheliya, exiled Island Prince turned masked thief. Silent thinker with sharp
                        instincts, dark desert-thief aesthetic with intense eyes. Transforms into a gigantic Winged Yali
                        to
                        challenge tyranny.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Kshala -->
                <div class="char-card">
                    <img src="images/Characters/KHSALA.png" alt="Kshala" class="char-img">
                    <h3>Kshala</h3>
                    <p class="role">Fearless Thief Girl - Moral Anchor</p>
                    <p class="bio">Survivor of the Silent Dawn Clan. Fierce but empathetic, bold and protective. Wears
                        the
                        Blue Crystal Pendant and teaches Ruthra: "Peace begins when the tongue stops reacting."</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Emperor Raya -->
                <div class="char-card">
                    <img src="images/Characters/Cheliya.png" alt="Emperor Raya" class="char-img">
                    <h3>Emperor Raya</h3>
                    <p class="role">Antagonist - The Sword Prince</p>
                    <p class="bio">Former prince who chose the Magic Sword of Pride. Tyrant ruler who killed his brother
                        Cheliya and Guru Kala to seize the throne. Wields the Dark Sword fueled by aggression and ego.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Sidh -->
                <div class="char-card">
                    <img src="images/Characters/Guru Kala.png" alt="Sidh" class="char-img">
                    <h3>Sidh</h3>
                    <p class="role">Wise Mentor - Minister of the Island</p>
                    <p class="bio">Son of Guru Kala who raised Ruthra in secret. Knows the truth of the relics and
                        protects
                        Ruthra from the Narabali (royal-blood sacrifice) prophecy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Locations -->
        <section id="locations" class="content-section alt-bg">
