                        INTERVAL: "THE TRUTH TAKES WINGS"
                    </h2>
                </div>

                <h3 style="color: var(--neon-purple); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">ACT 2: THE WINGED
                    WARRIOR
                </h3>
                <ol class="scene-list" start="11">
                    <li>The Hidden Chest - Ruthra's mother reveals Cheliya's rusted armguards and broken feathers</li>
                    <li>The Awakening Pulse - Armor responds to Ruthra's heartbeat, flashing memories</li>
                    <li>The Departure - Ruthra boards imperial barge carrying armor in secret</li>
                    <li>Underground Prison - Imprisoned in darkness, experiences Sparrow Dream</li>
                    <li>Transformation Spark - Escapes using partial, fleeting wings</li>
                    <li>Secret Meeting - Confirms the Sword's power is awakening</li>
                    <li>Reunion with Kshala - Plan to stop the Sword and free her tribe</li>
                    <li>Arena Trial - Emperor Raya challenges Ruthra to a duel</li>
                    <li>The Transformation of Dawn - Ruthra becomes Gigantic Winged Yali</li>
                    <li>The Flood - Redirects river to flood the capital, beginning countdown</li>
                    <li>Sky-Yali vs The Sword - Thunderous collision of Wings and Dark Sword fire</li>
                    <li>Treasury Heist - Kshala's tribe raids vaults, freeing captives</li>
                    <li>Yali Control Rhythm - Kshala's stone-clicks dissolve Ruthra's fear into clarity</li>
                    <li>Final Vision - The Sword's fire dies, Ruthra ends Raya with Sidh's help</li>
                    <li>New Dawn - Queen takes throne, ends slavery, Ruthra takes flight</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Synopsis -->
        <section id="synopsis" class="content-section alt-bg">
            <h2 class="section-title">SYNOPSIS</h2>
            <div class="container">
                <p>Late 6th century South India, during the Irundha Kaalam ("Dark Period")—a time of minimal political
                    records but rich spiritual wisdom. In the Cave of Destiny, two princes face an ancient choice: the
                    Magic
                    Sword of Pride or the Winged Armor of Awareness.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Prince Raya seizes the Sword, consumed by ambition. Prince Cheliya chooses the Wings, embracing
                    awareness. Raya becomes a tyrant emperor, murdering Cheliya and Guru Kala to claim absolute power.
                    But
                    Cheliya's son survives.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Ruthra grows up in secret on the Floating Rock Island, raised by Sidh (son of Guru Kala). As a masked
                    thief, he raids the Empire's tribute convoys, becoming a phantom legend. When he saves Kshala—a
                    fearless
                    thief from the Silent Dawn Clan—he learns the ancient Pazhi philosophy: observe before reacting,
                    face
                    fear with awareness.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Discovering the truth of his father's murder, Ruthra awakens the Winged Armor. The rusted relics
                    pulse
                    with life, and he transforms into a gigantic Winged Yali—a divine warrior bridging mortal and
                    celestial
                    realms. Emperor Raya, wielding the Dark Sword's demonic fire, prepares the Narabali sacrifice to
                    cement
                    his power.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Ruthra's plan: flood the capital by redirecting the river source behind Mahameru Palace. As the
                    waters
                    rise, the Sky-Yali and the Dark Sword collide in thunderous fury. Kshala performs the ancient Yali
                    control rhythm—stone-clicks, breath, gestures—dissolving Ruthra's fear into calm clarity. The
                    Sword's
                    fire dies.</p>
                <br>
                <p>With Sidh's help, Ruthra ends Raya's reign. The Queen takes the throne, decreeing an end to slavery
                    and
                    tyranny. As dawn breaks over the flooded Empire, Ruthra spreads his wings one last time, soaring
                    into
                    the new era—where awareness has conquered aggression, and the Karma Cycle finds balance.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

